.TH "rvt_reset_qp" 9 "rvt_reset_qp" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rvt_reset_qp \- initialize the QP state to the reset state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" rvt_reset_qp
.BI "(struct rvt_dev_info *rdi "  ","
.BI "struct rvt_qp *qp "  ","
.BI "enum ib_qp_type type "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rdi" 12
the device info
.IP "qp" 12
the QP to reset
.IP "type" 12
the QP type
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is the wrapper function to acquire the r_lock, s_hlock, and s_lock
before calling \fB_rvt_reset_qp\fP.
